Three track models are analysed afterwards, with an increasing degree of complexity:


the track on a rigid foundation (Fig. 2(a));

the track taking into account the soil through a Winkler's foundation, under the ballast (Fig. 2(b));

the track and the soil are completely coupled through the ballast stiffnesses acting between the sleepers and the soil surface, for a bidimensional track and a tridimensional soil (Fig. 2(c)). The soil is built with the FIEM approach, according to reference [22], and the ballast reactions are applied directly on a rectangular surface representing the sleeper area. The soil is defined with a vertical symmetry plane along the direction of the track.

